        Recipe(title: "Chuchvara", imageName: "chuchvara", serving: 4, preparationTime: 40, info: "Chuchvara is a popular traditional dish in Central Asia, particularly in Uzbekistan. It is a type of dumpling made with a filling of minced beef or lamb, onions, and spices, and is typically served in a clear broth or topped with sour cream or yogurt sauce.",
               ingredients: [Ingredients(name: "Minced beef", amount: "500g") ,Ingredients(name: "Salt/pepper", amount: "to taste" ),Ingredients(name: "Onion", amount: "2" ), Ingredients(name: "Garlic", amount: "2 cloves" ), Ingredients(name: "Cumin", amount: "1 teaspoon" ),Ingredients(name: "Coriander", amount: "1 teaspoon" ),Ingredients(name: "Flour", amount: "500g"),Ingredients(name: "Egg", amount: "1" ),Ingredients(name: "Water", amount: "2l" ), Ingredients(name: "Vegetable oil", amount: "200ml")],
               cookingGuide: [CookingGuide(step: 1, guide: "In a large mixing bowl, combine the minced meat, onions, garlic, salt, black pepper, cumin, and coriander. Mix well to combine the ingredients."), CookingGuide(step: 2, guide: "To make the dough, mix the flour, egg, and a pinch of salt in a separate bowl. Slowly add water and knead until the dough is smooth and elastic."), CookingGuide(step: 3, guide: "Roll out the dough on a floured surface and cut it into small squares."), CookingGuide(step: 4, guide: "Place a small amount of the meat mixture in the center of each square and fold the dough to form a small dumpling."), CookingGuide(step: 5, guide: "In a large pot, bring water to a boil and add the chuchvara. Cook for 10-15 minutes, or until the chuchvara floats to the top of the pot."), CookingGuide(step: 6, guide: "Serve hot, topped with sour cream or yogurt sauce, and garnished with fresh herbs if desired. Enjoy your delicious chuchvara!")]),


        Recipe(title: "Moshxo`rda", imageName: "moshxo'rda", serving: 5, preparationTime: 40, info: "Moshxo'rda (also spelled Moshkhora or Moshhurda) is a traditional Uzbek soup that is known for its rich flavors and hearty ingredients. It is a popular dish in Uzbekistan and is often enjoyed during the colder months or as a special occasion meal. Moshxo'rda is a beloved dish in Uzbek cuisine and showcases the rich culinary heritage of the region. It is not only delicious but also a hearty and nourishing meal that brings people together, particularly during family gatherings and celebrations.",
               ingredients: [Ingredients(name: "Lamb/beef", amount: "500g") , Ingredients(name: "Onion", amount: "1") ,Ingredients(name: "Carrot", amount: "3" ),Ingredients(name: "Potato", amount: "3" ), Ingredients(name: "Tomato", amount: "2" ), Ingredients(name: "Vegetable oil", amount: "200ml" ),Ingredients(name: "Garlic", amount: "2 cloves" ),Ingredients(name: "Cumin", amount: "1 teaspoon"),Ingredients(name: "Paprika", amount: "1" ),Ingredients(name: "Salt/pepper", amount: "to taste" ), Ingredients(name: "Mung beans", amount: "200g")],
               cookingGuide: [CookingGuide(step: 1, guide: "Use either a pot or a skillet deep enough to accommodate all the ingredients listed above. Turn the heat on high and pour the oil. Follow it up with the diced 1/2 lb meat. Brown the meat for about 5 minutes. Add diced onions and fry everything well. This step gives your dish a nice, rich color."), CookingGuide(step: 2, guide: "Turn the heat down to medium. Add chopped garlic and crushed tomatoes. Saute for about 5-6 minutes or until tomatoes are nicely softened"), CookingGuide(step: 3, guide: "Combination of carrots and beans is just fantastic. Add grated carrots into the pot and saute for 2 minutes."), CookingGuide(step: 4, guide: "Add 1 tsp cumin, 1/4 tsp black pepper, 2 tsp salt. Pour half of the boiled water into the pot. It will all look like a very thin soup. This is totally normal. Beans and rice will soak up all the water, creating a porridge like look."), CookingGuide(step: 5, guide: "Add washed mung beans and boiled black-eyed peas. Once the soup comes to boil, simmer it until mung beans “open up”. See attached photo."), CookingGuide(step: 6, guide: "Add washed 1 cup of rice. With a ladle or a wooden spoon mix everything well. Let the soup simmer and cook the rice. Rice will soak up most of the water, add water as necessary to avoid the bottom from burning. Also, if there is not enough water in the pot, the porridge will not cook well. Extra water can always be boiled out. I half-cover the lid of the pot to let the beans and rice get nice and soft. I also like Moshkichiri on a much softer, almost like a pudding soft texture. In different regions of Uzbekistan, this dish is enjoyed in different textures. Play with it and see what you enjoy better. Cooking down the porridge takes the most time. Cook until the desired texture is met. Do not forget to mix the pot periodically to open up the pressure on the bottom of the pan."), CookingGuide(step: 7, guide: "We really, really enjoy Moshkichiri with caramelized onions, yogurt, fresh herbs and with garlic chili sauce. Find the combo that works for you and enjoy this delicious dish.")])
